<title>CHILE: Telex-Chile receives cash from $75 mln loan.</title>
<headline>Telex-Chile receives cash from $75 mln loan.</headline>
<dateline>SANTIAGO 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Telex-Chile SA said its long-distance subsidiary Chilesat SA had finished the paper work and begun receiving funds from a $75 million syndicated loan led by Bank of America.</p>
<p>The loan, announced August 9, has a $65 million five-year portion and a $10 million, seven-year portion, Telex-Chile said in a statement.</p>
<p>The loan, which was well-received in the market and lifted Telex's share price, will allow the company to restructure some of its long-term debt.</p>
<p>-- Roger Atwood, Santiago newsroom +56-2-699-5595 x211</p>
